quotations.quotation: "That way, even before they step in, their room and arrival procedures will be set up in the exact manner they like," said Mr Olivier Lenoir, hotel manager, Grand Hyatt Singapore. "Their favourite pillow type, love of Earl Grey tea and even their language preference can now be recorded and delivered to our guests every time they check in, thus enriching their experience with us."

"The year started slower compared to last year," said Mr Patrick Fiat, general manager of Royal Plaza on Scotts. "This has impacted the room rates across the hotel industry. Room rates have dipped by 3 to 4 per cent while a good occupancy rate, which is similar to past years, has maintained for this year."

"In order to maintain Singapore’s lead, it is vital that hotels exceed guest expectations so as to encourage repeat visits and increase the length of (their) stay … After all, Singapore has the highest average room rates in Asia — guests expect real value for money," he said ...

quotations.quotation: "With corporate clients and delegates becoming increasingly concerned about the environment, business event organisers and meeting planners are turning to destinations and venues with strong sustainability policies in place," says Chew Tiong Heng, executive director of business tourism development for the Singapore Tourism Board. "Green initiatives are gaining traction among MICE event organisers, who recognise that such endeavours significantly enhance the overall visitor experience."

"We have seen an increasing trend of organisations adopting green practices and clients requesting green practice information from us," says RWS's communications manager, Clement Ng. 
"Sustainability is highlighted as part of the discussion with clients for the entire MICE package, where we encourage clients to adopt sustainable measures."

"We hope that our efforts in environmental protection will inspire our clients, partners and stakeholders to adopt responsible environmental and social practices, as well as drive the industry in that direction in the future," says MBS ...

"We actively encourage our customers and users to work with us to reduce wastage, recycle and reuse materials, to protect our environment and benefit the community," says a spokesman from HKCEC Management ...
"The concept of Go Green meetings aims to reduce our daily carbon footprint," says Carol Kong ...

"Regal Hotels has instituted corporate engagement initiatives that serve to inspire our guests, associates and other stakeholders to share our passion for sustainability," says Deven Leung, communications manager. "For instance, we have introduced green sales room and MICE packages to promote sustainable business growth."

"We have gone a step further to create a full green meeting package in which we not only just focus on our facilities and green meeting practices, but at the same time proactively promote the Community Engagement Programme and Cultural Heritage," says senior public relations manager Lily Cheng ...
"Special private meetings can be held at the Ocean Front Chapel, which has superb ocean views and is adjacent to a beach lawn," says the hotel's director of marketing, Joanna Lin ...
